params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.parent
params.description: Parent to retrieve services from. If this is set, the parent of all of the services specified in names must match this field. An example name would be: projects/123 where 123 is the project number. The BatchGetServices method currently only supports projects.

params.name: data.names
params.description: Names of the services to retrieve. An example name would be: projects/123/services/serviceusage.googleapis.com where 123 is the project number. A single request can get a maximum of 30 services at a time.
